 "VonburyResearch", "author_name": "Vonbury Research", "followers": 738, "views": 8174, "likes": 35, "replies": 4, "retweets": 5, "quotes": 2, "bookmarks": 3, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bullish", "emotional_sentiment": "Negative", "topics": ["US inventories", "Geopolitics"]}}, {"id": "2072206265493680164", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2072206265493680164", "text": "COLUMN: The hottest commodity? \n\nOne that's suffering from a major supply shock. It may sound like I’m talking about oil, but this is even more severe. Output is down 40% y-on-y and prices are up 80%.\n\nThe commodity in question? The anchovy. \n\n@Opinion https://t.co/tfgV2Ib8Vq", "time": "06:30", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 93859, "likes": 351, "replies": 33, "retweets": 70, "quotes": 17, "bookmarks": 82, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Neutral", "emotional_sentiment": "Positive", "topics": []}}, {"id": "2072238305513722056", "url": "https://x.com/antonisbabo/status/2072238305513722056", "text": "#oott outfit of the ton ㅎㅎ https://t.co/zvGVMoezQT", "time": "08:38", "author": "antonisbabo", "author_name": "바보", "followers": 39618, "views": 19539, "likes": 712, "replies": 0, "retweets": 188, "quotes": 6, "bookmarks": 62, "labels": {"relevant": false, "price_sentiment": "Neutral", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": []}}, {"id": "2072268044940804358", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2072268044940804358", "text": "In the first 4 months of 2026, US total oil production (crude, condensates and NGLs) has averaged 21.33m b/d — that's &gt;900,000 b/d higher than in same period of 2025. And that's before the US shale industry had the opportunity to react to (and hedge) ~$100 a barrel.", "time": "10:36", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 37505, "likes": 184, "replies": 17, "retweets": 29, "quotes": 0, "bookmarks": 9, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bearish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Shale/US production"]}}, {"id": "2072288733156594134", "url": "https://x.com/staunovo/status/2072288733156594134", "text": "#Russia buys gasoline from #India to tackle shortages, sources say\nAt least 60,000 metric tons shipped from India, two sources say\nRussian fuel shortage has led to rationing, queues, price spikes\n#oott https://t.co/UXymXAlzeX", "time": "11:58", "author": "staunovo", "author_name": "Giovanni Staunovo🛢", "followers": 120883, "views": 18622, "likes": 13, "replies": 1, "retweets": 6, "quotes": 3, "bookmarks": 0, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bullish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Russia sanctions", "Refining/products"]}}, {"id": "2072292131528483075", "url": "https://x.com/DeItaone/status/2072292131528483075", "text": "OPEC+ IS LIKELY TO RAISE OIL OUTPUT QUOTAS FOR AUGUST BY 188,000 BARRELS PER DAY AT SUNDAY MEETING, THREE SOURCES SAY\n\n#OOTT", "time": "12:12", "author": "DeItaone", "author_name": "*Walter Bloomberg", "followers": 1688831, "views": 121483, "likes": 177, "replies": 24, "retweets": 23, "quotes": 3, "bookmarks": 6, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bearish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["OPEC+"]}}, {"id": "2072323484030541892", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2072323484030541892", "text": "🚨🚨🚨 We have the first Persian Gulf country lifting its oil exports to (if not even above) pre-war levels: UAE.\n\nSure, the 'ketchup effect' may be inflating exports a bit (from inventories). But whatever that contribution is, clearly June oil exports have surged to >95% of pre-war levels (and some ta", "time": "14:16", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 206225, "likes": 590, "replies": 36, "retweets": 106, "quotes": 14, "bookmarks": 77, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bearish", "emotional_sentiment": "Positive", "topics": ["Supply outlook", "Tankers/shipping"]}}, {"id": "2072327228252143861", "url": "https://x.com/LiveSquawk/status/2072327228252143861", "text": "#OOTT | US DoE Crude Oil Inventories (W/W) 01-Jul: -3.775M (est -2.903M; prev -6.088M)\n- Distillate: 2.483M (est +10.20K; prev +3.064M)\n- Cushing: +709K (prev -1.077M)\n- Gasoline: -2.333M (est +559.60K; prev +2.064M)\n- Refinery: +0.50% (est -0.31%; prev -0.60%)", "time": "14:31", "author": "LiveSquawk", "author_name": "LiveSquawk", "followers": 436344, "views": 16644, "likes": 9, "replies": 0, "retweets": 3, "quotes": 1, "bookmarks": 0, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bullish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["US inventories"]}}, {"id": "2072331209904886023", "url": "https://x.com/Amena__Bakr/status/2072331209904886023", "text": "A little over 5 million bpd of crude oil exited Hormuz in June… don’t let the numbers fool you that’s just a 1/3 of normal flows pre war . #OOTT", "time": "14:47", "author": "Amena__Bakr", "author_name": "Amena Bakr", "followers": 174705, "views": 90674, "likes": 490, "replies": 41, "retweets": 80, "quotes": 9, "bookmarks": 31, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bullish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Tankers/shipping", "Iran"]}}, {"id": "2072332626073915469", "url": "https://x.com/staunovo/status/2072332626073915469", "text": "Charts on US petroleum inventories in million barrels (EIA) #oott https://t.co/9Im4cFzGum", "time": "14:52", "author": "staunovo", "author_name": "Giovanni Staunovo🛢", "followers": 120883, "views": 11068, "likes": 70, "replies": 6, "retweets": 19, "quotes": 0, "bookmarks": 19, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Neutral", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["US inventories"]}}, {"id": "2072335331744186724", "url": "https://x.com/avionsunantiqu1/status/2072335331744186724", "text": "PADD2 got a bit of extra oil (almost all of which went to Cushing), suggesting PADD2 (not just Cushing) may be very close to Tank Bottoms.\n\nIs this the start of the Mayhem Trump was talking about?#OOTT https://t.co/p4bDRf2h1o", "time": "15:03", "author": "avionsunantiqu1", "author_name": "Nicholas James", "followers": 1433, "views": 11936, "likes": 94, "replies": 2, "retweets": 10, "quotes": 2, "bookmarks": 8, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bullish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["US inventories"]}}, {"id": "2072338254578196676", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2072338254578196676", "text": "WTI prompt time-spread flirting with contango.", "time": "15:15", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 87901, "likes": 119, "replies": 11, "retweets": 6, "quotes": 3, "bookmarks": 8, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Bearish", "emotional_sentiment": "Neutral", "topics": ["Prices/technicals"]}}, {"id": "2072345546157621722", "url": "https://x.com/JavierBlas/status/2072345546157621722", "text": "CHART OF THE DAY: The hottest commodity? \n\nIt isn't oil or fertiliser. The commodity in question is weathering an even greater supply shock and record prices: The anchovy — and its derivative, fishmeal (key for global aquaculture).\n\nMy @Opinion column: https://t.co/f7q7NRui58 https://t.co/zwcqxXMaPC", "time": "15:44", "author": "JavierBlas", "author_name": "Javier Blas", "followers": 393796, "views": 51098, "likes": 178, "replies": 16, "retweets": 49, "quotes": 8, "bookmarks": 28, "labels": {"relevant": true, "price_sentiment": "Neutral", "emotional_sentiment": "Positive", "topics": []}}, {"id": "2072391434951385311", "url": "https://x.com/aeberman12/status/2072391434951385311", "text": "WTI is $11 less than its implied marginal price at current comparative inventory level\n\nInventories say $85 but markets say $74\n\nMarkets have undershot as price discovery proceeds\n#energy #OOTT #oilandgas #WTI #CrudeOil #fintwit #OPEC #Commodities #commoditiesmarket https://t.co/u6k62XYO0r", "time": "18:46", "